<subSubSection id="C3485ED60958B206EC95FE97236A4FA3" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BED0D5D0958B206EC95FE97251D4B4C" blockId="12.[151,1437,331,610]" box="[151,1302,331,358]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0958B206EC95FE9721294B4C" bold="true" box="[151,290,331,357]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">Etymology:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0958B206ED2BFE9021904B4F" authorityName="Heckel" authorityYear="1843" box="[297,411,332,358]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Cyprinion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0958B206ED2BFE9021904B4F" box="[297,411,332,358]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">Cyprinion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: diminutive of Latin, 
<emphasis id="B926D14F0958B206EE93FE9022FA4B4C" box="[657,753,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">cyprinus</emphasis>
= carp; 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0958B206EF45FE9023C34B4C" baseAuthorityName="Boulenger" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[839,968,332,357]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Cyprinion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="muscatense">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0958B206EF45FE9023C34B4C" box="[839,968,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">muscatense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: composed from 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD0958B206E88FFE9024D44B4F" box="[1165,1247,332,358]" name="Oman" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">Muscat</collectingCountry>
city.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BED0D5D0958B206ECC5FEB322FE4BA0" blockId="12.[151,1437,331,610]" box="[199,757,367,394]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0958B206ECC5FEB3218C4BA0" bold="true" box="[199,391,367,393]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">Common name:</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD0958B206ED8CFEAC21EB4BA3" box="[398,480,368,394]" name="Oman" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">Muscat</collectingCountry>
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0958B206EDEAFEB322FE4BA0" authority=", Hajar Lotak." authorityName="Hajar Lotak." box="[488,757,367,393]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Cyprinion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Cyprinion, Hajar Lotak.</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BED0D5D0958B206ECC5FE4F2106484B" blockId="12.[151,1437,331,610]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0958B206ECC5FE4F21454B84" bold="true" box="[199,334,403,429]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">Taxonomy:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0958B206ED54FE4F22624B84" authorityName="Boulenger" authorityYear="1888" box="[342,617,403,429]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Scaphiodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="muscatensis">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0958B206ED54FE4F22624B84" box="[342,617,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">Scaphiodon muscatensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by Boulenger [G. A.] 1888:665 [Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London 1887 (pt 4) from 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD0958B206EE79FE6422DB4BFB" box="[635,720,440,466]" name="Oman" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">Muscat</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD0958B206EED8FE6B232A4BF8" box="[730,801,439,465]" name="Oman" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">Oman</collectingCountry>
, Gulf of 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD0958B206EF80FE6B23C24BF8" box="[898,969,439,465]" name="Oman" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">Oman</collectingCountry>
, Arabian Sea, northwestern Indian Ocean. 
<emphasis id="B926D14F0958B206EC95FE0721094BDC" box="[151,258,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">
<typeStatus id="54E9B3FF0958B206EC95FE0720F74BDC" box="[151,252,475,501]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">Syntypes</typeStatus>
:
</emphasis>
BMNH 1885.11.7.35-40 (6), 1887.11.11.289-291 (3). It was considered as synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0958B206E8D8FE0021AE4830" authority="(Day, 1880)" baseAuthorityName="Day" baseAuthorityYear="1880" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Cyprinion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="microphthalmum">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0958B206E8D8FE00211E4830" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">Cyprinion microphthalmum</emphasis>
(Day, 1880)
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC370AC0958B206EDD1FE2322FC4830" author="Banister, K. E. &amp; Clarke, M. A." box="[467,759,511,537]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" pagination="111 - 154" refId="ref22687" refString="Banister, K. E. &amp; Clarke, M. A. (1977) The freshwater fishes of the Arabian Peninsula. The scientific results of the Oman flora and fauna survey 1975. Journal of Oman Studies, Special Report, 1977, 111 - 154." type="journal article" year="1977">Banister &amp; Clarke (1977)</bibRefCitation>
:130 and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC370AC0958B206EF5DFE2324934833" author="Alkahem, H. F. &amp; Behnke, R. J." box="[863,1176,511,538]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" pagination="545 - 567" refId="ref22655" refString="Alkahem, H. F. &amp; Behnke, R. J. (1983) Freshwater fishes of Saudi Arabia. Fauna Saudi Arabia, 5, 545 - 567." type="journal article" year="1983">Alkahem &amp; Behnke (1983)</bibRefCitation>
:559; 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0958B206E8DAFDDC21AF4814" authority="(Day, 1880)" baseAuthorityName="Day" baseAuthorityYear="1880" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Cyprinion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="microphthalmum">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0958B206E8DAFDDC211E4814" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">Cyprinion microphthalmum</emphasis>
(Day, 1880)
</taxonomicName>
, but a valid subspecies by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC370AC0958B206EED2FDF823614814" author="Krupp, F." box="[720,874,547,574]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" pagination="568 - 636" refId="ref24500" refString="Krupp, F. (1983) Freshwater fishes of Saudi Arabia and adjacent regions of the Arabian Peninsula. Fauna of Saudi Arabia, 5, 568 - 636." type="journal article" year="1983">Krupp (1983)</bibRefCitation>
589; and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0958B206EFD8FDF8253C4814" authority="(Day, 1872)" baseAuthorityName="Day" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[986,1335,547,574]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Cyprinion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="watsoni">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0958B206EFD8FDF824A14814" box="[986,1194,548,574]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">Cyprinion watsoni</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC370AC0958B206E8BBFDFF25254814" author="Day, F." box="[1209,1326,547,573]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" pagination="258 - 260" refId="ref23046" refString="Day, F. (1872) Notes on fish, collected by Dr. Stoliczka in Kachh. Journal of the Asiatic Society of Bengal, 41 (Pt. 2, No. 1 - 4), 258 - 260." type="journal article" year="1872">Day, 1872</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC370AC0958B206E963FDFF20E3484B" author="Coad, B. W." pageId="12" pageNumber="463" pagination="1 - 64" refId="ref22961" refString="Coad, B. W. (1995) Freshwater fishes of Iran. Acta Scientiarum Naturalium Academiae Scientiarum Bohemicae, Brno, 29 (1), 1 - 64." type="journal article" year="1995">Coad (1995)</bibRefCitation>
:16.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF2D5DD50958B206EC95FBAA22954EA7" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6541591" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6541591" box="[151,670,1142,1166]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6541591/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" startId="12.[151,250,1142,1166]" targetBox="[151,1436,633,1118]" targetPageId="12">
<paragraph id="8BED0D5D0958B206EC95FBAA22954EA7" blockId="12.[151,670,1142,1166]" box="[151,670,1142,1166]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0958B206EC95FBAA212B4EA7" bold="true" box="[151,288,1142,1166]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">FIGURE 12.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0958B206ED24FBAB22034EA7" baseAuthorityName="Boulenger" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[294,520,1143,1166]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Cyprinion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="463" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="muscatense">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0958B206ED24FBAB22034EA7" box="[294,520,1143,1166]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">Cyprinion muscatense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, Oman: Surur.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BED0D5D0958B206ECC5FB60236A4FA3" blockId="12.[151,1437,1212,1817]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0958B206ECC5FB6021AB4EFF" bold="true" box="[199,416,1212,1238]" pageId="12" pageNumber="463">Short description:</emphasis>
D III, 10–11; A II, 7; LL 37–41; L.tr. 4. Length of head one fourth of total (without caudal); diameter of eye one fourth the barbel on each side, measuring three fifths the diameter of the eye; mandible sharp, with a horny sheath. Origin of dorsal just above the ventrals, midway between the end of the snout and the base of the caudal; last undivided dorsal ray osseous, rather feeble, not serrated. Pectoral as long as the head less the snout. Caudal forked. Bronzy above, whitish below; scales, except the lowermost, with a dark brown margin; a moderately distinct blackish lateral band ending in a spot before the caudal.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
